WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:11.094 --> 00:00:12.012 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
What am I supposed to do now?

00:00:12.095 --> 00:00:13.179 position:50% align:center
[GINJI]
You asking me for help?

00:00:13.263 --> 00:00:14.305 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
This isn't your way of saying

00:00:14.389 --> 00:00:15.432 position:50% align:center
you'll join my party, is it?

00:00:15.515 --> 00:00:16.975 position:50% align:center
What kind of help did you mean?

00:00:17.058 --> 00:00:19.102 position:50% align:center
[GINJI]
The best kind I can offer.

00:00:19.185 --> 00:00:21.730 position:50% align:center
We got ourselves
a criminal in here!

00:00:21.813 --> 00:00:25.400 position:50% align:center
Tell City Guard it's
the Best Friend Killer!

00:00:25.483 --> 00:00:28.778 position:50% align:center
But-- I-- How could you?

00:00:28.862 --> 00:00:30.113 position:50% align:center
[GINJI]
Take it from me, kid:

00:00:30.196 --> 00:00:32.157 position:50% align:center
try not to botch
the interrogation.

00:00:32.240 --> 00:00:33.616 position:50% align:center
Make a good enough impression

00:00:33.700 --> 00:00:35.827 position:50% align:center
and they may even let
you off the hook.

00:00:35.910 --> 00:00:39.497 position:50% align:center
You... You're kidding me.

00:00:39.581 --> 00:00:40.540 position:50% align:center
[GUARD A]
There he is!

00:00:40.623 --> 00:00:42.125 position:50% align:center
[GUARD B]
Grab him!

00:00:44.669 --> 00:00:46.296 position:50% align:center
So, you're our fugitive, huh?

00:00:46.379 --> 00:00:50.050 position:50% align:center
I hereby arrest you on
suspicion of foul play!

00:02:28.398 --> 00:02:29.774 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
Gimme a break!

00:02:29.858 --> 00:02:33.695 position:50% align:center
How'd they get here so fast?
That's not realistic!

00:02:33.778 --> 00:02:37.032 position:50% align:center
Helluva time for game logic
to kick in all of a sudden.

00:02:37.115 --> 00:02:39.534 position:50% align:center
The warrant!
It's all above board!

00:02:39.617 --> 00:02:42.412 position:50% align:center
Hold on. I can explain.

00:02:42.495 --> 00:02:43.747 position:50% align:center
[AMOS]
Hey!

00:02:43.830 --> 00:02:45.790 position:50% align:center
[GINJI]
No ya don't!

00:02:47.459 --> 00:02:49.753 position:50% align:center
Would someone mind takin'
over from here, please?

00:02:49.836 --> 00:02:51.755 position:50% align:center
My gout's flarin' up on me!

00:02:51.838 --> 00:02:52.756 position:50% align:center
[HIRO groans]

00:02:52.839 --> 00:02:54.716 position:50% align:center
[GINJI grunts]

00:02:54.799 --> 00:02:58.678 position:50% align:center
Let go! Seriously... I can't!

00:02:58.762 --> 00:03:01.222 position:50% align:center
[GINJI]
You sound like a rooster.

00:03:02.265 --> 00:03:06.770 position:50% align:center
[HIRO] Arthritis my ass,
this dude is strong!

00:03:09.022 --> 00:03:10.190 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
Great.

00:03:10.273 --> 00:03:14.694 position:50% align:center
The developers nailed
getting choked out, too.

00:03:14.778 --> 00:03:17.906 position:50% align:center
Right. Thanks for the help,
but that's quite enough.

00:03:17.989 --> 00:03:22.077 position:50% align:center
[HIRO gasping, coughing]

00:03:22.160 --> 00:03:24.454 position:50% align:center
[GINJI laughs]
Not to impose, sir.

00:03:24.537 --> 00:03:27.582 position:50% align:center
But surely I've earned
myself another round.

00:03:27.665 --> 00:03:31.961 position:50% align:center
You're an incorrigible
miscreant. Here.

00:03:33.129 --> 00:03:35.256 position:50% align:center
Ah! Much obliged.

00:03:35.340 --> 00:03:39.219 position:50% align:center
Ha! Right, sure, I get it,
Mr. Upstanding Citizen.

00:03:39.302 --> 00:03:40.887 position:50% align:center
[GINJI]
Shut up, newbie.

00:03:40.970 --> 00:03:42.514 position:50% align:center
Trust me. Say nothin'.

00:03:42.597 --> 00:03:44.099 position:50% align:center
Whatever crap they
try to pull on you,

00:03:44.182 --> 00:03:46.184 position:50% align:center
don't admit to killin' anybody.

00:03:46.267 --> 00:03:49.896 position:50% align:center
Well, 'less you're keen on doing
hard time, like yours truly.

00:03:49.979 --> 00:03:53.108 position:50% align:center
You went to prison?
But it's just a game!

00:03:53.191 --> 00:03:55.402 position:50% align:center
Yup. Gave 13 years of my life.

00:03:55.485 --> 00:03:57.654 position:50% align:center
Luckily at the moment
I'm on parole.

00:03:57.737 --> 00:03:59.906 position:50% align:center
What the hell is wrong with you?
That's crazy talk!

00:03:59.989 --> 00:04:02.867 position:50% align:center
For 13 years, every time you
logged on you were in jail?

00:04:02.951 --> 00:04:04.828 position:50% align:center
How 'bout just
quitting the game?

00:04:04.911 --> 00:04:07.163 position:50% align:center
Ask my pals Enrique and Marie.

00:04:07.247 --> 00:04:10.792 position:50% align:center
Cheers! So much
for options, kiddo!

00:04:10.875 --> 00:04:13.503 position:50% align:center
'Kay, this guy's clearly
got some issues.

00:04:13.586 --> 00:04:17.257 position:50% align:center
Enough! Move your ass.
Not another syllable.

00:04:17.340 --> 00:04:21.511 position:50% align:center
[groans] Look, if you want
quiet, stop kicking me!

00:04:21.594 --> 00:04:23.013 position:50% align:center
Is that a fact?

00:04:23.096 --> 00:04:24.222 position:50% align:center
[HIRO yelps]

00:04:24.305 --> 00:04:25.724 position:50% align:center
[MAN A] Doesn't look
like much of a killer.

00:04:25.807 --> 00:04:27.350 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN A]
What? That's nonsense.

00:04:27.434 --> 00:04:29.185 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN B] The glint
in his eye says it all.

00:04:29.269 --> 00:04:31.604 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN C]
Lowly brute.

00:04:31.688 --> 00:04:33.398 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
Ugh. Jeez.

00:04:33.481 --> 00:04:35.567 position:50% align:center
Do we have to do this
whole walk of shame?

00:04:35.650 --> 00:04:37.694 position:50% align:center
Worst cutscene ever.

00:04:37.777 --> 00:04:39.571 position:50% align:center
All right, then. This'll do.

00:04:39.654 --> 00:04:41.364 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:04:42.615 --> 00:04:43.783 position:50% align:center
What the--?

00:04:43.867 --> 00:04:47.328 position:50% align:center
Who the hell threw that?
Real mature, you guys!

00:04:47.412 --> 00:04:49.122 position:50% align:center
--[MAN B] Animal!
--[MAN C] Murderer!

00:04:49.205 --> 00:04:52.000 position:50% align:center
--[MAN D] You're a disgrace!
--[WOMAN D] Friend killer!

00:04:52.083 --> 00:04:53.376 position:50% align:center
Hey! Would ya cut it out?!

00:04:53.460 --> 00:04:55.962 position:50% align:center
That hurts!
What is going on here?

00:04:56.046 --> 00:04:59.299 position:50% align:center
Stone Time's what
Ted is famous for.

00:04:59.382 --> 00:05:01.051 position:50% align:center
Oh, come on! Really? Stone Time?

00:05:01.134 --> 00:05:02.594 position:50% align:center
I hate to be the one
to tell you this,

00:05:02.677 --> 00:05:04.763 position:50% align:center
but vigilante justice
is not a good look!

00:05:04.846 --> 00:05:06.473 position:50% align:center
--[MAN C] Silence!
--[WOMAN D] You bastard!

00:05:06.556 --> 00:05:07.807 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN E]
He's a maniac!

00:05:07.891 --> 00:05:11.227 position:50% align:center
Damn it! You're an officer!
Make them stop!

00:05:11.311 --> 00:05:13.355 position:50% align:center
I don't enjoy it
any more than you do.

00:05:13.438 --> 00:05:16.649 position:50% align:center
I get caught in the crossfire.

00:05:16.733 --> 00:05:18.360 position:50% align:center
Okay, Stone Time's over!

00:05:18.443 --> 00:05:21.654 position:50% align:center
Quit it! Hey!
That means you, ass hat!

00:05:21.738 --> 00:05:24.157 position:50% align:center
Step away from the pumpkin!

00:05:24.240 --> 00:05:25.200 position:50% align:center
[MAN B]
Lame.

00:05:25.283 --> 00:05:26.659 position:50% align:center
[MAN E]
Well, that didn't last long.

00:05:26.743 --> 00:05:28.161 position:50% align:center
[MAN F]
When's the next one?

00:05:28.244 --> 00:05:30.372 position:50% align:center
[MAN G] I don't know, but
I'm bringing flagstones.

00:05:30.455 --> 00:05:32.916 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
Damn it. This is bull crap!

00:05:32.999 --> 00:05:35.335 position:50% align:center
I'm supposed to be
the protagonist!

00:05:35.418 --> 00:05:37.253 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:05:37.337 --> 00:05:40.298 position:50% align:center
[GODDESS A]
Hale and well met, mighty hero!

00:05:40.382 --> 00:05:44.010 position:50% align:center
The world of Auberdine
needs your help!

00:05:44.094 --> 00:05:45.970 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
Um, hey!

00:05:46.054 --> 00:05:48.932 position:50% align:center
Now what?
Your shackles too tight?

00:05:49.015 --> 00:05:51.101 position:50% align:center
I demand you release me at once!

00:05:51.184 --> 00:05:54.729 position:50% align:center
Your incompetence
imperils the city.

00:05:54.813 --> 00:05:56.981 position:50% align:center
What are you babbling about?

00:05:57.065 --> 00:05:59.359 position:50% align:center
This may test the
limits of belief,

00:05:59.442 --> 00:06:01.986 position:50% align:center
but you are addressing a hero.

00:06:02.070 --> 00:06:03.988 position:50% align:center
[AMOS grunting]

00:06:04.072 --> 00:06:06.366 position:50% align:center
You heard correctly.
Don't be surprised

00:06:06.449 --> 00:06:09.369 position:50% align:center
if one day the king himself
appeals for my help!

00:06:09.452 --> 00:06:11.496 position:50% align:center
Saving the world from
the forces of darkness

00:06:11.579 --> 00:06:13.289 position:50% align:center
falls upon me and me alone!

00:06:13.373 --> 00:06:15.875 position:50% align:center
Yet I bear the burden with
the stoicism of a true--

00:06:15.959 --> 00:06:17.752 position:50% align:center
Not you, too.

00:06:17.836 --> 00:06:20.547 position:50% align:center
Do I look stupid? If I had
a gald for every crackpot

00:06:20.630 --> 00:06:23.466 position:50% align:center
who's spewed that exact same
garbage, I could retire!

00:06:23.550 --> 00:06:25.343 position:50% align:center
Ugh! Where does it end?

00:06:25.427 --> 00:06:26.636 position:50% align:center
Wait. That's not...

00:06:26.720 --> 00:06:28.179 position:50% align:center
I mean, you're supposed to...

00:06:28.263 --> 00:06:30.640 position:50% align:center
You delinquents always think
pleading insanity will get you

00:06:30.724 --> 00:06:33.518 position:50% align:center
a lighter sentence. Well,
I've got news for you, kid!

00:06:33.601 --> 00:06:37.105 position:50% align:center
The concept of leniency
is way above my pay grade!

00:06:37.188 --> 00:06:39.649 position:50% align:center
[HIRO] Uh. I can't even
play the hero card

00:06:39.733 --> 00:06:43.445 position:50% align:center
to get out of jail? Who asked
for this level of authenticity?

00:06:43.528 --> 00:06:44.946 position:50% align:center
Come on. Let's move.

00:06:45.030 --> 00:06:46.698 position:50% align:center
For all the supposed
benefits of this gig,

00:06:46.781 --> 00:06:49.200 position:50% align:center
my rank isn't eligible
for overtime.

00:06:49.284 --> 00:06:50.952 position:50% align:center
Wow. That really sucks, dude.

00:06:51.036 --> 00:06:54.789 position:50% align:center
Okay, fine, sure, whatever.
I'll go quietly.

00:06:54.873 --> 00:06:56.416 position:50% align:center
Uh?

00:07:05.342 --> 00:07:08.094 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
Oh, no. Alicia!

00:07:08.178 --> 00:07:09.929 position:50% align:center
Damn it, my eye!

00:07:10.013 --> 00:07:14.100 position:50% align:center
Coward! I will hunt you
down and eviscerate you!

00:07:14.184 --> 00:07:16.978 position:50% align:center
Not her...

00:07:17.062 --> 00:07:18.772 position:50% align:center
[HIRO screaming]

00:07:18.855 --> 00:07:20.231 position:50% align:center
Okay! Let's get moving!

00:07:20.315 --> 00:07:22.901 position:50% align:center
Throw me in a dungeon!
I don't care! Just hurry!

00:07:22.984 --> 00:07:24.819 position:50% align:center
Hey! Don't take that
tone with me, son!

00:07:24.903 --> 00:07:27.113 position:50% align:center
We go when I say we go!

00:07:28.281 --> 00:07:31.326 position:50% align:center
[MONSTER A roaring]

00:07:31.409 --> 00:07:34.662 position:50% align:center
[HIRO groans]

00:07:34.746 --> 00:07:37.290 position:50% align:center
I'd make myself at home in
there if I were you, murderer.

00:07:37.374 --> 00:07:40.293 position:50% align:center
Oh, and don't bother being
tempted by dreams of escape.

00:07:40.377 --> 00:07:43.046 position:50% align:center
Believe me. Ha, ha.

00:07:45.382 --> 00:07:49.302 position:50% align:center
Dumb prick. Ugh. Seriously?

00:07:50.553 --> 00:07:53.848 position:50% align:center
[HIRO grunts]
Okay. Solid.

00:07:55.767 --> 00:07:58.311 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
Screw this. I'm logging out.

00:07:58.395 --> 00:08:01.648 position:50% align:center
Way to show up in my
hour of need, Reona.

00:08:05.318 --> 00:08:07.404 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
What? Are you kidding?

00:08:07.487 --> 00:08:11.533 position:50% align:center
That's not how this works!
Let me the hell out of here!

00:08:15.203 --> 00:08:16.871 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:08:27.048 --> 00:08:29.134 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
It's been like an hour.

00:08:29.217 --> 00:08:32.220 position:50% align:center
In game time that's
basically an entire day.

00:08:32.303 --> 00:08:35.974 position:50% align:center
How long am I gonna be
stuck in this joint?

00:08:36.057 --> 00:08:38.727 position:50% align:center
I cannot handle this.

00:08:49.946 --> 00:08:51.865 position:50% align:center
[HIRO growls]

00:08:57.620 --> 00:09:02.042 position:50% align:center
Come on! This is ridiculous!
How long can one "event" be?

00:09:02.125 --> 00:09:03.293 position:50% align:center
[stomach grumbles]

00:09:03.376 --> 00:09:05.462 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
Perfect. Now I'm hungry.

00:09:05.545 --> 00:09:09.883 position:50% align:center
Why would you incorporate
real hunger into a game?!

00:09:16.264 --> 00:09:18.808 position:50% align:center
Awesome. Well, this sucks.

00:09:18.892 --> 00:09:21.269 position:50% align:center
Now I have to take a leak, too.

00:09:21.353 --> 00:09:25.815 position:50% align:center
Uh?

00:09:25.899 --> 00:09:27.442 position:50% align:center
Least there's a toilet.

00:09:27.525 --> 00:09:32.030 position:50% align:center
'Cept with my luck it's
probably my wash basin, too.

00:09:32.113 --> 00:09:34.783 position:50% align:center
[HIRO sniffing]

00:09:34.866 --> 00:09:36.534 position:50% align:center
Ugh. Okay, again.

00:09:36.618 --> 00:09:39.746 position:50% align:center
I don't need this kind
of realism, thanks.

00:09:41.956 --> 00:09:44.959 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
Huh?

00:09:45.043 --> 00:09:47.462 position:50% align:center
[yelps]

00:09:49.589 --> 00:09:53.093 position:50% align:center
[HIRO] That was close!
I almost broke the seal!

00:09:56.012 --> 00:09:57.847 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
What am I looking at?

00:09:57.931 --> 00:09:59.349 position:50% align:center
A monster?

00:09:59.432 --> 00:10:04.688 position:50% align:center
No, it's gotta be an NPC.
But I was the only one in here!

00:10:04.771 --> 00:10:06.189 position:50% align:center
Hiro...

00:10:06.272 --> 00:10:08.233 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:10:08.316 --> 00:10:11.194 position:50% align:center
How could you? You fiend.

00:10:11.277 --> 00:10:15.699 position:50% align:center
Hold on. That physique.
And wait, that voice, too!

00:10:17.534 --> 00:10:20.954 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
Martin? Is that you?

00:10:21.037 --> 00:10:24.749 position:50% align:center
How's that even...?
I mean, you're totally...

00:10:24.833 --> 00:10:27.919 position:50% align:center
That is to say, because I...

00:10:28.003 --> 00:10:30.296 position:50% align:center
That's right. It is I.

00:10:30.380 --> 00:10:33.591 position:50% align:center
Your old friend.
Whom you so mercilessly...

00:10:33.675 --> 00:10:34.843 position:50% align:center
...killed!

00:10:34.926 --> 00:10:38.179 position:50% align:center
Oh, great! When did this
become a horror game?

00:10:38.263 --> 00:10:40.640 position:50% align:center
[HIRO gasping]

00:10:40.724 --> 00:10:43.393 position:50% align:center
Look. I'm really sorry!
I didn't mean to!

00:10:43.476 --> 00:10:46.646 position:50% align:center
The dagger in my throat
tells a different story.

00:10:46.730 --> 00:10:49.357 position:50% align:center
This was intended. You fiend!

00:10:49.441 --> 00:10:51.359 position:50% align:center
--No, no! Hold on!
--[MARTIN]  Yes.

00:10:51.443 --> 00:10:53.319 position:50% align:center
That's not how it went down,
I swear!

00:10:53.403 --> 00:10:55.905 position:50% align:center
You were eating apple slices!

00:11:02.412 --> 00:11:03.997 position:50% align:center
One moment I
was helping myself

00:11:04.080 --> 00:11:06.958 position:50% align:center
to an apple slice and
then, out of the blue,

00:11:07.042 --> 00:11:09.586 position:50% align:center
I'm sprawled on the
floor like carrion.

00:11:09.669 --> 00:11:12.922 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:11:13.006 --> 00:11:16.676 position:50% align:center
[MARTIN] You laugh.
Do you find that funny?

00:11:16.760 --> 00:11:19.137 position:50% align:center
No! Sorry! Just--

00:11:19.220 --> 00:11:22.223 position:50% align:center
Hiro. Do you remember
our promise?

00:11:22.307 --> 00:11:25.977 position:50% align:center
The oath we swore to one another
beneath the Kenura tree?

00:11:26.061 --> 00:11:27.979 position:50% align:center
I-- I remember you
saying something about

00:11:28.063 --> 00:11:30.565 position:50% align:center
a stupid tree, but that's
all I got, really!

00:11:30.648 --> 00:11:33.151 position:50% align:center
Say it! Recite the sacred vow

00:11:33.234 --> 00:11:36.029 position:50% align:center
we made under its
branches that fateful day!

00:11:36.112 --> 00:11:37.238 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
What's he talking about?

00:11:37.322 --> 00:11:38.698 position:50% align:center
Is it covered in the manual?

00:11:38.782 --> 00:11:39.783 position:50% align:center
Wait, that's dumb.

00:11:39.866 --> 00:11:41.493 position:50% align:center
Games don't have
manuals in them anymore.

00:11:41.576 --> 00:11:45.455 position:50% align:center
Go on! What were the exact
words of our promise?

00:11:45.538 --> 00:11:48.458 position:50% align:center
[HIRO] I don't know!
Hear me out!

00:11:48.541 --> 00:11:50.919 position:50% align:center
I know we're supposed to
be old pals and all that,

00:11:51.002 --> 00:11:54.422 position:50% align:center
but I only just
started this game!

00:11:54.506 --> 00:11:57.801 position:50% align:center
Is that so? Well,
this changes things.

00:11:57.884 --> 00:12:00.136 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
So, we're on the same page?

00:12:00.220 --> 00:12:03.973 position:50% align:center
Until your memory returns,
I'll haunt you day and night.

00:12:04.057 --> 00:12:05.266 position:50% align:center
Why is that the answer?

00:12:05.350 --> 00:12:08.186 position:50% align:center
I can't remember something
I never experienced!

00:12:08.269 --> 00:12:11.606 position:50% align:center
I shall call this endeavor...
Martin Time!

00:12:11.690 --> 00:12:14.442 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
Um, how 'bout we not?

00:12:14.526 --> 00:12:16.236 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
Wait a minute.

00:12:18.655 --> 00:12:21.282 position:50% align:center
[HIRO] Ginji's haunted by
his best friend, isn't he?

00:12:21.366 --> 00:12:23.785 position:50% align:center
As a matter of fact,
come to think of it,

00:12:23.868 --> 00:12:27.080 position:50% align:center
he implied there
were two ghosts.

00:12:27.163 --> 00:12:31.459 position:50% align:center
[HIRO grunts]
Uh. What're you doing?

00:12:31.543 --> 00:12:35.547 position:50% align:center
[MARTIN]
Such potential. Such promise.

00:12:35.630 --> 00:12:36.798 position:50% align:center
[HIRO whimpers]

00:12:36.881 --> 00:12:39.718 position:50% align:center
Why must I be dead?!

00:12:39.801 --> 00:12:43.513 position:50% align:center
[HIRO screams]
Okay! That's it!

00:12:43.596 --> 00:12:44.931 position:50% align:center
I'd like to be done now!

00:12:45.015 --> 00:12:48.184 position:50% align:center
Reona! What's taking
you so long?

00:12:48.268 --> 00:12:53.064 position:50% align:center
Somebody! Help!
All I wanna do is log off!

00:12:53.148 --> 00:12:54.858 position:50% align:center
[MIZARISA]
It's okay. I'm comin'!

00:12:54.941 --> 00:12:56.443 position:50% align:center
Reona, 's that you?

00:12:56.526 --> 00:12:58.862 position:50% align:center
You sure as heck took your
sweet ass time finding me!

00:12:58.945 --> 00:13:02.532 position:50% align:center
[MIZARISA] Sorry to disappoint
you, but that's not my name.

00:13:02.615 --> 00:13:04.743 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:13:04.826 --> 00:13:06.870 position:50% align:center
Don't really care!
Just get me out!

00:13:06.953 --> 00:13:08.079 position:50% align:center
It's Martin Time!

00:13:08.163 --> 00:13:10.832 position:50% align:center
Which evidently means
I'm haunted forever!

00:13:10.915 --> 00:13:12.375 position:50% align:center
Whoa. Everything okay?

00:13:12.459 --> 00:13:14.127 position:50% align:center
What in the world's
going on in there?

00:13:14.210 --> 00:13:15.462 position:50% align:center
Wha--? Well, let's see.

00:13:15.545 --> 00:13:17.339 position:50% align:center
I'm caked in blood,
so that freakin' sucks!

00:13:17.422 --> 00:13:20.175 position:50% align:center
Hate to contradict you, but
there's no blood I can see.

00:13:20.258 --> 00:13:22.427 position:50% align:center
Just get me out of here!
I'm beggin' ya!

00:13:22.510 --> 00:13:24.012 position:50% align:center
Fine! Just try to calm down.

00:13:24.095 --> 00:13:26.139 position:50% align:center
Take a deep breath
and count to ten.

00:13:26.222 --> 00:13:28.933 position:50% align:center
I believe you're
the one called Hiro?

00:13:29.017 --> 00:13:31.895 position:50% align:center
It's gonna be okay, don't worry.

00:13:33.897 --> 00:13:35.982 position:50% align:center
Um, so what do I call you?

00:13:36.066 --> 00:13:39.944 position:50% align:center
Who, me? Ah...
My name's Mizarisa. Hi.

00:13:40.028 --> 00:13:41.905 position:50% align:center
Pleased to make
your acquaintance.

00:13:41.988 --> 00:13:44.366 position:50% align:center
Yeah--where are we
going, exactly?

00:13:44.449 --> 00:13:46.242 position:50% align:center
[MIZARISA]
You'll see.

00:13:56.878 --> 00:13:59.214 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
A bed?

00:13:59.297 --> 00:14:02.092 position:50% align:center
'Kay. You lost me.

00:14:05.470 --> 00:14:06.888 position:50% align:center
Relax. You, my friend,

00:14:06.971 --> 00:14:09.015 position:50% align:center
are about to have
the time of your life.

00:14:09.099 --> 00:14:13.395 position:50% align:center
Uh? I am? But--

00:14:13.478 --> 00:14:17.774 position:50% align:center
"Intense stimulation?" What
is that supposed to mean?

00:14:17.857 --> 00:14:20.860 position:50% align:center
Is-- are we about to get...?

00:14:23.905 --> 00:14:26.950 position:50% align:center
[HIRO] Is she inviting me
to do the do?

00:14:27.033 --> 00:14:29.577 position:50% align:center
[gulps]

00:14:36.334 --> 00:14:37.460 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
I mean...

00:14:37.544 --> 00:14:40.296 position:50% align:center
If this game is the
ultimate in realism...

00:14:40.380 --> 00:14:41.756 position:50% align:center
And I can feel pain.

00:14:41.840 --> 00:14:46.094 position:50% align:center
Seems only fair that I
can feel other things.

00:14:46.177 --> 00:14:47.470 position:50% align:center
Wait. No.

00:14:47.554 --> 00:14:49.764 position:50% align:center
This isn't the content
I signed up for.

00:14:49.848 --> 00:14:53.685 position:50% align:center
I just wanted a pure
and wholesome RPG!

00:14:53.768 --> 00:14:57.939 position:50% align:center
Except fully immersive does
mean fully immersive,

00:14:58.023 --> 00:15:00.358 position:50% align:center
and if it's integral
to the story...

00:15:00.442 --> 00:15:04.070 position:50% align:center
This experience fleshes out
my character arc--literally!

00:15:04.154 --> 00:15:06.239 position:50% align:center
Score!

00:15:07.824 --> 00:15:11.327 position:50% align:center
Why don't you lay your pretty
little self down on the bed?

00:15:11.411 --> 00:15:14.080 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
Oh-ho! Yes, ma'am!

00:15:20.170 --> 00:15:22.547 position:50% align:center
Good. Now, close those
beautiful eyes.

00:15:22.630 --> 00:15:24.924 position:50% align:center
Absolutely.

00:15:26.593 --> 00:15:31.348 position:50% align:center
[HIRO] She's getting undressed!
This is really happening!

00:15:31.431 --> 00:15:34.517 position:50% align:center
I know this trope.
She's a naughty prison guard.

00:15:34.601 --> 00:15:37.187 position:50% align:center
Man, if this is what it
means to do hard time,

00:15:37.270 --> 00:15:41.483 position:50% align:center
give me 13 years without
the possibility of parole!

00:15:41.566 --> 00:15:46.905 position:50% align:center
Ah! You know what?
I take it back.

00:15:46.988 --> 00:15:50.408 position:50% align:center
Slap my ass with
a life sentence!

00:15:52.160 --> 00:15:53.787 position:50% align:center
Woof. Here it comes!

00:15:53.870 --> 00:15:56.998 position:50% align:center
[MIZARISA] Easy.
Keep those eyes closed.

00:15:57.082 --> 00:15:59.459 position:50% align:center
Uh. You got it.

00:16:04.464 --> 00:16:06.966 position:50% align:center
Ah. There now, 'kay?

00:16:07.050 --> 00:16:09.344 position:50% align:center
Have a look at what's in store.

00:16:09.427 --> 00:16:11.096 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh.

00:16:18.770 --> 00:16:21.314 position:50% align:center
Oh. That's an interesting look.

00:16:26.569 --> 00:16:28.738 position:50% align:center
Wait, what?

00:16:28.822 --> 00:16:31.408 position:50% align:center
Um, full disclosure: this may
be a little advanced for--

00:16:31.491 --> 00:16:33.576 position:50% align:center
[MIZARISA giggles]
Get ready!

00:16:33.660 --> 00:16:35.120 position:50% align:center
Today's your lucky day!

00:16:35.203 --> 00:16:37.997 position:50% align:center
This is what we like to
call Inquisition Time!

00:16:38.081 --> 00:16:40.291 position:50% align:center
Like dirty inquisition?

00:16:40.375 --> 00:16:42.585 position:50% align:center
Cool. I can be down with that!

00:16:42.669 --> 00:16:44.838 position:50% align:center
Oh, I have something
a little more traditional

00:16:44.921 --> 00:16:49.426 position:50% align:center
in mind for you. Mizarisa the
Inquisitor at your service.

00:16:49.509 --> 00:16:50.969 position:50% align:center
Ah, sweet! Role play!

00:16:51.052 --> 00:16:54.264 position:50% align:center
You know, I've always
been curious about S&amp;M.

00:16:54.347 --> 00:16:56.016 position:50% align:center
Because my womanly
intuition tells me

00:16:56.099 --> 00:16:57.851 position:50% align:center
that's the demon
inside you talking,

00:16:57.934 --> 00:17:00.812 position:50% align:center
I'ma kick this lil party off
with a standard exorcism.

00:17:00.895 --> 00:17:02.147 position:50% align:center
Um. Okay.

00:17:02.230 --> 00:17:04.858 position:50% align:center
Not sure how that goes,
but cool. Sign me up!

00:17:04.941 --> 00:17:07.610 position:50% align:center
[MIZARISA] Here's the
deal--break under torture

00:17:07.694 --> 00:17:09.988 position:50% align:center
and confess, I take you
back to your cell.

00:17:10.071 --> 00:17:12.741 position:50% align:center
Hold out past the limits of
endurance, Martin's murder

00:17:12.824 --> 00:17:15.368 position:50% align:center
gets blamed on the demon
and you're a free man.

00:17:15.452 --> 00:17:18.538 position:50% align:center
Best of luck, Hiro.

00:17:18.621 --> 00:17:21.207 position:50% align:center
So what kinda
torture we talkin'?

00:17:21.291 --> 00:17:23.626 position:50% align:center
Hot wax? Whips and chains?

00:17:23.710 --> 00:17:27.589 position:50% align:center
[MIZARISA]
My personal favorite.

00:17:27.672 --> 00:17:30.592 position:50% align:center
Amputation of the arms and legs!

00:17:30.675 --> 00:17:34.137 position:50% align:center
Okay, is there a safe word?

00:17:36.014 --> 00:17:38.475 position:50% align:center
[screams] Hell no!

00:17:38.558 --> 00:17:39.726 position:50% align:center
Ohh! Yes!

00:17:39.809 --> 00:17:41.978 position:50% align:center
That's what I like to
hear from my subjects.

00:17:42.062 --> 00:17:44.814 position:50% align:center
Keep screaming!
That's so hot!

00:17:44.898 --> 00:17:47.442 position:50% align:center
[HIRO]
No, no, no, no! Reona!

00:17:47.525 --> 00:17:50.737 position:50% align:center
Help me! Another crazy girl
with a sharp object!

00:17:50.820 --> 00:17:52.572 position:50% align:center
[REONA]
What is going on?

00:17:52.655 --> 00:17:53.823 position:50% align:center
What do you think?

00:17:53.907 --> 00:17:55.533 position:50% align:center
What took you so
long to get here?

00:17:55.617 --> 00:17:57.619 position:50% align:center
I logged on hours ago
and it's been hell!

00:17:57.702 --> 00:17:59.704 position:50% align:center
This entire day has sucked ass!

00:17:59.788 --> 00:18:01.873 position:50% align:center
Gosh. I'm so sorry.

00:18:01.956 --> 00:18:04.834 position:50% align:center
I was kind of in the
middle of something.

00:18:04.918 --> 00:18:06.378 position:50% align:center
No, it's okay.
Don't be sorry.

00:18:06.461 --> 00:18:08.672 position:50% align:center
You fended off Alicia for me
like a trooper and I'm sure

00:18:08.755 --> 00:18:10.799 position:50% align:center
running the game shop
keeps you super busy.

00:18:10.882 --> 00:18:13.218 position:50% align:center
Actually, I just got roped
into watching Miyazaki's

00:18:13.301 --> 00:18:15.303 position:50% align:center
<i>Castle in the Sky</i> for the
umpteenth time and lost

00:18:15.387 --> 00:18:16.763 position:50% align:center
track of when you messaged me.

00:18:16.846 --> 00:18:18.890 position:50% align:center
Come on! Like we don't
all know that movie

00:18:18.973 --> 00:18:20.725 position:50% align:center
forward and backwards
by now!

00:18:20.809 --> 00:18:22.519 position:50% align:center
A masterpiece yields
fresh discoveries

00:18:22.602 --> 00:18:24.813 position:50% align:center
with each subsequent viewing!
That's why it's art!

00:18:24.896 --> 00:18:26.815 position:50% align:center
Plus, I was live-tweeting
the broadcast, so, you know.

00:18:26.898 --> 00:18:30.151 position:50% align:center
[HIRO] Does my present condition
scream "give a damn?"

00:18:30.235 --> 00:18:31.486 position:50% align:center
Talking to yourself?

00:18:31.569 --> 00:18:34.447 position:50% align:center
Oop. That's not an
encouraging sign, I'm afraid.

00:18:34.531 --> 00:18:37.075 position:50% align:center
Methinks the fear is
driving you whacka-do.

00:18:37.158 --> 00:18:37.992 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:18:38.076 --> 00:18:39.494 position:50% align:center
Don't fall apart now.

00:18:39.577 --> 00:18:42.831 position:50% align:center
At least wait to lose your mind
till I've broken the skin.

00:18:42.914 --> 00:18:45.625 position:50% align:center
[HIRO whimpering]
Reona!

00:18:45.709 --> 00:18:48.044 position:50% align:center
That pointy part's getting
uncomfortably close to my bits!

00:18:48.128 --> 00:18:52.465 position:50% align:center
[REONA]
I got you! Sparkle! Ah!

00:18:52.549 --> 00:18:56.970 position:50% align:center
Hiro, Hiro! He's our man!
If he can't do it, no one can!

00:18:57.053 --> 00:18:58.388 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:18:58.471 --> 00:19:00.140 position:50% align:center
I know this isn't what you
want to hear, but enduring

00:19:00.223 --> 00:19:02.934 position:50% align:center
the torture is surest path to
being cleared of all charges,

00:19:03.018 --> 00:19:04.936 position:50% align:center
so I'm encouraging you
as best I can!

00:19:05.020 --> 00:19:07.022 position:50% align:center
I will cheer until
my voice breaks!

00:19:07.105 --> 00:19:09.399 position:50% align:center
Dammit, I need saving,
not a pep talk!

00:19:09.482 --> 00:19:12.152 position:50% align:center
Well excuse me for not being
able to break shackles!

00:19:12.235 --> 00:19:14.612 position:50% align:center
I should've taken my
chances with the ghost!

00:19:14.696 --> 00:19:17.699 position:50% align:center
Less babble,
more severed limbs!

00:19:20.618 --> 00:19:24.748 position:50% align:center
Ah! Oh, crap, this is happening!
Hey, please don't...

00:19:24.831 --> 00:19:26.875 position:50% align:center
I have zero pain tolerance!

00:19:26.958 --> 00:19:29.669 position:50% align:center
[laughs] Which leg do I choose?

00:19:29.753 --> 00:19:31.212 position:50% align:center
The right leg is
practically begging

00:19:31.296 --> 00:19:33.340 position:50% align:center
to be separated
from the rest of you!

00:19:33.423 --> 00:19:38.094 position:50% align:center
Don't do this!

00:19:38.178 --> 00:19:39.554 position:50% align:center
[HIRO gasps]

00:19:49.564 --> 00:19:52.567 position:50% align:center
Um, Hiro? I think you
just peed yourself.

00:19:52.650 --> 00:19:55.987 position:50% align:center
Is that even a thing
someone your age still does?

00:19:56.071 --> 00:19:58.740 position:50% align:center
[laughs] Glorious!

00:19:58.823 --> 00:20:01.951 position:50% align:center
Stupendous!
What a gratifying accident!

00:20:02.035 --> 00:20:05.622 position:50% align:center
That tracks...
like everything else in life.

00:20:05.705 --> 00:20:08.124 position:50% align:center
I've been an Inquisitor
for 12 years now

00:20:08.208 --> 00:20:12.671 position:50% align:center
and never before have I seen
someone so humiliated!

00:20:14.798 --> 00:20:16.091 position:50% align:center
Such luck!

00:20:16.174 --> 00:20:18.218 position:50% align:center
Getting to amputate a
thoroughly piss-soaked leg!

00:20:18.301 --> 00:20:20.428 position:50% align:center
Ahh! I love this job!

00:20:20.512 --> 00:20:22.847 position:50% align:center
Stay with me, Hiro!
I believe in you!

00:20:22.931 --> 00:20:25.725 position:50% align:center
I am done!

00:20:25.809 --> 00:20:29.479 position:50% align:center
I give up. Everything
in my life is trash.

00:20:29.562 --> 00:20:32.023 position:50% align:center
Don't say that.

00:20:32.107 --> 00:20:36.778 position:50% align:center
I just... there's
no point anymore.

00:20:38.905 --> 00:20:41.700 position:50% align:center
Then what's a little mutilation?

00:20:43.243 --> 00:20:45.745 position:50% align:center
[AMOS] Hold it!
The Interrogation's off!

00:20:45.829 --> 00:20:49.290 position:50% align:center
